data.text:
Clean Lyric

Paragraph Lyric

Sometimes I forget I'm so asleep

Sometimes I just trip between my dreams

If I wake up then please close the door

I've lost my dignity and so much more

You are the one I know as love

And I'm so unlovely

You are the one I know as love

And I'm not deserving

You are the one I know as life

and I'm not done living

You are the one, the only one

That has been worth giving

To myself

There is a place we go to show off our skin

There is a face I know I have to kiss

Should there be hopes to start to sputter fast

I am the one who gets to hold you last
